-- Skoda Auto Recalls 24,000 Fabias In China Because of Software, CTK Reports
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-10-07T05:37:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-07/skoda-auto-recalls-24-000-fabias-in-china-because-of-software-ctk-reports.html
Skoda Auto AS, the Czech unit of
Volkswagen AG, is recalling 24,000 of its Fabia models in China
to servis due to a software problem that could cause the motor
to switch off, CTK agency reported, citing spokesman Evzen
Krauskopf.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  